The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 31: Indias external debt has increased by $31.8 billion in first nine months of the fiscal to $201.4 billion (around Rs 7,94,017 crore), caused by a spurt in overseas borrowings by companies and rupee appreciation. It implied that with a total population of about 110 crore, per capita debt on each Indian stood at Rs 7,218. According to a finance ministry statement, the external debt increased $10.3 billion in the third quarter this fiscal.                            
	 Mumbai, March 31: A wide import-export gap led to Indias current account deficit rising to $5.4 billion in the third quarter of 2007-08, despite a higher surplus of earnings from software services, tourism and remittances from abroad.                            
	 New Delhi, March 31: Stung by the steel industrys campaign on curbing iron ore exports, miners today said India had a surplus of 112 million tonnes of ore and asked the government to determine actual production by steel utilities to bring them under tax to augment state revenue.                            
	 Mumbai, March 31: JM Financial has become the 100 per cent owner of JM Financial Ask Securities by buying the remaining 40 per cent stake of the company from the Ask group for Rs 81 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, March 31: The RBI today allowed trading in power bonds that were issued by states to the central public sector undertakings and are set to mature in October 2012 and April 2013.                                                                                                                           
